#Approach:

💡 IDEA
- Har window ka first negative number chahiye.
- Queue me sirf negative numbers store karenge.
- Queue ka front hamesha current window ka first negative hoga.

⚙️ APPROACH
1. First k elements process karo.
   - Agar element negative hai → queue me daalo.

2. Ab har new window ke liye:
   - Queue empty hai → answer = 0
   - Otherwise → answer = queue.front

3. Window slide karo:
   - Agar outgoing element queue ke front ke equal hai:
     usko remove karo.
   - Agar new incoming element negative hai:
     queue me add karo.

4. Last window ka answer bhi add kar do.

📝 EXAMPLE

arr = [-8, 2, 3, -6, 10]
k = 2

First Window:
[-8, 2]

Queue = [-8]

Answer = -8

----------------

Slide

Window:
[2, 3]

Outgoing = -8

Queue Front = -8
remove it

Queue = []

No negative present

Answer = 0

----------------

Slide

Window:
[3, -6]

Insert -6

Queue = [-6]

Answer = -6

----------------

Slide

Window:
[-6, 10]

Queue Front = -6

Answer = -6

Final:
[-8, 0, -6, -6]

❓ WHY QUEUE
- Queue arrival order maintain karti hai.
- First negative hamesha front par milta hai.
- Positive numbers completely ignore kar sakte hain.
- Sirf useful (negative) elements store hote hain.

⏱️ COMPLEXITY
Time  : O(N)

Reason:
- Har negative element maximum ek baar add hota hai.
- Har negative element maximum ek baar remove hota hai.

Space : O(K)
         (Worst case: poori window negative)

🎯 INTERVIEW POINT
- Queue me sirf negative numbers store ho rahe hain.
- Front = current window ka first negative.
- Outgoing element remove tabhi karna hai jab wo queue ke front par ho.
- Positive elements queue me kabhi nahi jaate.
- Sliding Window + Queue ka classic pattern:
  "Store only useful candidates".

#Code:

import java.util.*;

public class Solution
{
    public List<Integer> firstNegative(int[] arr, int n, int k)
    {
        //You can code here
        ArrayDeque<Integer> dq = new ArrayDeque<>();
        List<Integer> ans = new ArrayList<>();

        int i = 0;
        while(i < k){
          if(arr[i] < 0){
            dq.offerLast(arr[i]);
          }
          i++;
        }

        for(; i<n; i++){
          //if dq is empty
          if(dq.isEmpty()){
            ans.add(0);
          }else{
            ans.add(dq.peekFirst());
          }

          if(!dq.isEmpty() && dq.peekFirst() == arr[i-k]){
            dq.pollFirst();
          }

          if(arr[i] < 0){
            dq.offerLast(arr[i]);
          }
        }

        //putting element based on last window
        if(dq.isEmpty()){
          ans.add(0);
        }
        else{
          ans.add(dq.peekFirst());
        }
        return ans;
      
    }
}
